<TITLE> Learner driver held after killing DU prof's wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 22 (bdnews24.com)The police held the learner driver of a private car after he ran over and killed Anima Rani Saha, a Dhaka University professor's wife, taking a morning walk near Jagannath Hall east gate on Monday. The driver, 22 year-old Fahim, is a student of Dhaka Medical College and a resident of Shahjahanpur in the capital, Shahbagh police chief Rezaul Karim said. Anima, wife of Parimal Kumar Saha of DU's Institute of Education Research, was taken to DMC Hospital at around 7am, Rezaul said. She was pronounced dead at the hospital, he said. Witnesses said Fahim lost control of his vehicle and drove onto the footpath, running over the professor's wife. Angry DU students set fire to the car following the accident. bd
